#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Rule"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Godhikasutta"
msgstr "23. With Godhika"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.121"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.265"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā godhiko isigilipasse viharati kāḷasilāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Godhika was staying on the slopes of Isigili at "
"the Black Rock."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Godhika, meditating diligent, keen, and resolute, experienced "
"temporary freedom of heart."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihāyi."
msgstr "But then he fell away from that temporary freedom of heart."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.6"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr "For a second …"

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihāyi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.8"
msgid ""
"Tatiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr "third …"

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.9"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā … pe … parihāyi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.10"
msgid "Catutthampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto … pe … vimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr "fourth …"

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.11"
msgid "Catutthampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā … pe … parihāyi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.12"
msgid "Pañcamampi kho āyasmā godhiko … pe … cetovimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr "fifth …"

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.13"
msgid "Pañcamampi kho āyasmā … pe … vimuttiyā parihāyi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.14"
msgid ""
"Chaṭṭhampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr "sixth time Godhika experienced temporary freedom of heart."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.15"
msgid "Chaṭṭhampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihāyi."
msgstr "But for a sixth time he fell away from it."

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.16"
msgid ""
"Sattamampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ phusi."
msgstr ""
"For a seventh time Godhika, meditating diligent, keen, and resolute, "
"experienced temporary freedom of heart."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.266"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato godhikassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "sn4.23:2.2"
msgid "“yāva chaṭṭhaṃ khvāhaṃ sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihīno."
msgstr ""
"“I’ve fallen away from this temporary freedom of heart no less than six "
"times."

msgctxt "sn4.23:2.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ satthaṃ āhareyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I slit my wrists?”"

msgctxt "sn4.23:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā āyasmato godhikassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"And then Māra the Wicked, knowing what Godhika was thinking, went up to the "
"Buddha and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.1"
msgid "“Mahāvīra mahāpañña,"
msgstr "“O great hero, O greatly wise!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.2"
msgid "iddhiyā yasasā jala;"
msgstr "Shining with power and glory."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.3"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātīta,"
msgstr "You’ve gone beyond all threats and perils,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.4"
msgid "pāde vandāmi cakkhuma."
msgstr "I bow to your feet, O seer!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.1"
msgid "Sāvako te mahāvīra,"
msgstr "Great hero, master of death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.2"
msgid "maraṇaṃ maraṇābhibhū;"
msgstr "your disciple longs for death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.3"
msgid "Ākaṅkhati cetayati,"
msgstr "he’s planning for it."

# A rather curious epithet for Mara to use. It is identical with “Lucifer”. http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=lucifer
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.4"
msgid "taṃ nisedha jutindhara."
msgstr "Stop him, O light-bringer!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.1"
msgid "Kathañhi bhagavā tuyhaṃ,"
msgstr "For how, Blessed One, can a disciple of yours,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.2"
msgid "Sāvako sāsane rato;"
msgstr "one who loves your teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.3"
msgid "Appattamānaso sekkho,"
msgstr "a trainee who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.4"
msgid "Kālaṃ kayirā janesutā”ti."
msgstr "take his own life, O renowned one?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:6.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmatā godhikena satthaṃ āharitaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Godhika had already slit his wrists."

msgctxt "sn4.23:6.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, addressed him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.267"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.1"
msgid "“Evañhi dhīrā kubbanti,"
msgstr "“This is how the wise act,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.2"
msgid "nāvakaṅkhanti jīvitaṃ;"
msgstr "for they don’t long for life."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.3"
msgid "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha,"
msgstr "Having plucked out craving, root and all,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.4"
msgid "godhiko parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "Godhika is extinguished.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn4.23:8.2"
msgid ""
"“āyāma, bhikkhave, yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkamissāma yattha "
"godhikena kulaputtena satthaṃ āharitan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Come, mendicants, let’s go to the Black Rock on the slopes of Isigili where "
"Godhika, who came from a good family, slit his wrists.”"

msgctxt "sn4.23:8.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.122"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:9.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā "
"tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with several mendicants went to the Black Rock on "
"the slopes of Isigili."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/turning-shoulders-and-casting-off-aggregates/2949
#. VAR: semānaṃ → soppamānaṃ (si, mr) | seyyamānaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.23:9.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ godhikaṃ dūratova mañcake vivattakkhandhaṃ "
"semānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha saw Godhika off in the distance lying on his cot, having cast off "
"the aggregates."

msgctxt "sn4.23:9.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena dhūmāyitattaṃ timirāyitattaṃ gacchateva purimaṃ "
"disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ "
"disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ, gacchati adho, gacchati anudisaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a cloud of black smoke was moving east, west, north, south, "
"above, below, and in-between."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.268"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.2"
msgid ""
"“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ dhūmāyitattaṃ timirāyitattaṃ gacchateva "
"purimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati "
"dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ, gacchati adho, gacchati anudisan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, do you see that cloud of black smoke moving east, west, north, "
"south, above, below, and in-between?”"

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.4"
msgid ""
"“Eso kho, bhikkhave, māro pāpimā godhikassa kulaputtassa viññāṇaṃ "
"samanvesati:"
msgstr ""
"“That’s Māra the Wicked searching for Godhika’s consciousness, wondering:"

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.5"
msgid "‘kattha godhikassa kulaputtassa viññāṇaṃ patiṭṭhitan’ti?"
msgstr "‘Where is Godhika’s consciousness established?’"

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.6"
msgid ""
"Appatiṭṭhitena ca, bhikkhave, viññāṇena godhiko kulaputto parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr ""
"But since his consciousness is not established, Godhika is extinguished.”"

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā beluvapaṇḍuvīṇaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra, carrying his harp of yellow wood apple, went up to the Buddha and "
"addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.1"
msgid "“Uddhaṃ adho ca tiriyaṃ,"
msgstr "“Above, below, and all around,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.2"
msgid "disā anudisā svahaṃ;"
msgstr "in the four quarters and in-between,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.3"
msgid "Anvesaṃ nādhigacchāmi,"
msgstr "I’ve been searching without success:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.4"
msgid "godhiko so kuhiṃ gato”ti."
msgstr "where has that Godhika got to?”"

# reading so
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. VAR: Yo → so (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.1"
msgid "“Yo dhīro dhitisampanno,"
msgstr "“He was a wise and steadfast sage,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.2"
msgid "jhāyī jhānarato sadā;"
msgstr "a meditator who loved to practice absorption."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.3"
msgid "Ahorattaṃ anuyuñjaṃ,"
msgstr "By day and by night he applied himself,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.4"
msgid "jīvitaṃ anikāmayaṃ."
msgstr "without concern for his life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.1"
msgid "Jetvāna maccuno senaṃ,"
msgstr "He defeated the army of death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.2"
msgid "anāgantvā punabbhavaṃ;"
msgstr "and won’t return for any future life."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.3"
msgid "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha,"
msgstr "Having plucked out craving root and all"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.4"
msgid "godhiko parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "Godhika is extinguished.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.269"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.1"
msgid "Tassa sokaparetassa,"
msgstr "Stricken with sorrow,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.2"
msgid "vīṇā kacchā abhassatha;"
msgstr "his harp dropping from his armpit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.3"
msgid "Tato so dummano yakkho,"
msgstr "that spirit, downcast,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: tatthevantaradhāyathāti → tatthevantaradhāyithāti (s1-3, km) | tatthevantaradhayathāti (pts1) | tattheva antaradhāyīti (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.4"
msgid "tatthevantaradhāyathāti."
msgstr "vanished right there."
